IN THE 1940'S MANY CUSTODIAL PEOPLE LIVED IN THE BUILDINGS THAT THEY KEPT CLEAN.
THE PRIMARY SPEAKER REMEMBERS TELLING HIS PARENTS THAT THEY WERE RICH.
HIS PARENTS SAID THEY WERE FAR FROM RICH.
THEY MOVED INTO A LIBRARY BECAUSE HIS FATHER GOT A JOB AS A CUSTODIAN IN THE LIBRARY.
GROWING UP HE THOUGHT THAT KIDS THOUGHT HE WAS DIFFERENT BECAUSE HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
HE REALIZED THAT LIVING IN A LIBRARY WAS FUN.
HE HAD TO BE QUIET DURING THE DAY, BUT AT NIGHT HE WAS ALLOWED TO RUN AND SCREAM IN THE LIBRARY.
IF HE WANTED TO LEARN SOMETHING, HE WOULD JUST GO TO THE LIBRARY AND GET A BOOK TO READ ABOUT WHAT HE WANTED TO LEARN.
HE WOULD STAY UP SOMETIMES UNTIL 3 AM READING BOOKS.
HIS FATHER MADE SURE TO POLISH AND WAX THE FLOOR EVERYDAY.
HIS FATHER EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE BOOKCASES, SO WHEN YOU WALKED UP THE STAIRS YOU COULD SEE HOW CLEAN AND SHINY THE TOP OF THE BOOKCASES WAS.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO ATTEND COLLEGE AND GRADUATE.
HE BROUGHT HIS DAD TO HIS WORK ONE DAY TO SHOW HIS FATHER HIS CLASSROOM.
ON THE DOOR OF HIS CLASSROOM, WAS HIS NAME ON A PLAQUE.
THE STORY WAS BASED IN THE 1940'S.
A BOY LIVED WITH HIS PARENTS IN A PLACE AND HE THOUGHT THAT THEY WERE RICH.
MANY CUSTODIANS LIVED IN THE BUILDINGS IN WHICH THEY WORKED.
HIM AND HIS FAMILY MOVED INTO A LIBRARY WHERE HIS DAD WAS GOING TO BE THE CUSTODIAN.
HIS DAD WAXED NOT ONLY THE FLOORS, BUT THE TOP OF THE BOOKSHELVES.
WHEN PEOPLE CAME UP THE STAIRS YOU COULD SEE THE SHINE ON THE TOP OF THE BOOK SHELVES.
THE BOY WOULD HAVE TO BE VERY QUIET DURING THE DAY, BUT AT NIGHT HE COULD RUN AND SCREAM THROUGH THE LIBRARY.
HE DIDNT INVITE ANY FRIENDS OVER BECAUSE HE THOUGHT THEY MAY THINK IT WEIRD THAT HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
IF HE EVER WANTED TO KNOW ANYTHING HE WOULD JUST GO TO THE LIBRARY AND GET A BOOK ABOUT IT.
HE WOULD SPEND NUMEROUS HOURS READING BOOKS AND WOULD SOMETIMES STAY UP UNTIL 3AM READING BOOKS.
HE WAS THE FIRST PERSON IN HIS FAMILY TO NOT ONLY GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL, BUT ONLY COLLEGE.
HE BECAME A PROFESSOR AND HE WAS SO PROUD TO BRING HIS DAD TO HIS WORK.
HIS NAME WAS ON HIS DOOR AND HIS DAD WAS VERY QUIET WHEN HE SHOWED HIM THAT.
